HEADWORD: Sixty-fourth
<hw>Six`ty-fourth"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Constituting or
being one of sixty-four equal parts into which a thing is
divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sixty-fourth note</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>the
sixty-fourth part of a whole note; a hemi-demi-semiquaver.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sizable</ent>⟦br⟧
